definition.value: Plasmopara viticola, the causal agent of grapevine downy mildew, is a heterothallic oomycete that overwinters as oospores in leaf litter and soil.
Marchantia polymorpha subsp. polymorpha is one of the three subspecies of Marchantia polymorpha.

label.value: Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Enteritidis

definition.value: Xanthomonas translucens pv. cerealis is the causal agent of bacterial leaf streak on true grasses. Xanthomonas translucens pv. cerealis has been found on crops, like wheat (Triticum spp.), barley (Hordeum spp.), and rye (Secale cereale), and it also naturally occurs on smooth bromegrass and quack grass.
